        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 5:00PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 500 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Mount Vernon. This
storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud
to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Vernon, Ailey, Tarrytown, and Kibbee.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
